  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Floor Captain (Dempsey Hill)",
  "description": "<h3>About AIR CCCC</h3><p>AIR CCCC is a vibrant restaurant located in the heart of Dempsey Hill, offering a versatile and welcoming space suitable for all kinds of events—from casual dining and private celebrations to corporate functions and special occasions. We pride ourselves on warm hospitality, quality service, and creating memorable experiences for every guest.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>We are looking for enthusiastic and service-oriented Floor Captain/Service Crew to join our team. As part of the front-of-house team, you will play a key role in delivering excellent customer service and ensuring smooth daily operations, especially during events and peak periods.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Greet and attend to guests in a friendly and professional manner</p></li><li><p>Take food and beverage orders accurately and efficiently</p></li><li><p>Serve food and drinks promptly, ensuring presentation and quality standards are met</p></li><li><p>Set up and clear tables, including event and function setups</p></li><li><p>Assist with event service, including private parties and corporate bookings</p></li><li><p>Handle guest feedback and requests politely and efficiently</p></li><li><p>Maintain cleanliness and hygiene of the dining and service areas</p></li><li><p>Work closely with kitchen and bar staff to ensure smooth service flow</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Positive attitude and strong customer service mindset</p></li><li><p>Ability to work in a fast-paced environment</p></li><li><p>Good communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Willingness to work flexible hours, including weekends and public holidays</p></li><li><p>Prior F&B or event service experience is an advantage, but not required</p></li><li><p>Team player with a proactive and responsible attitude</p></li></ul><h3>What We Offer</h3><ul><li><p>Friendly and supportive work environment</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to gain experience in restaurant and event service</p></li><li><p>5 days work week</p></li><li><p>Staff meals and other benefits (where applicable)</p></li></ul>",
